Exploratory Analysis: Plot the Time Series

italianUnemploymentRate <- ts(italianUnemployment$unemployment_rate, 
            start = c(2020, 1),  # Year and period (e.g., month)
            frequency = 12)      
plot(italianUnemploymentRate)

Exploratory Analysis: run ACF

# Differencing to remove trend
italianUnemploymentRate_diff <- diff(italianUnemploymentRate)

# Plot differenced series to verify stationarity
plot(italianUnemploymentRate_diff)

# Calculate ACF of differenced series
Acf(italianUnemploymentRate_diff)

Naive Model

naive_forecast <- naive(italianUnemploymentRate,6)
plot(naive_forecast)

Simple Average Model

avg_forecast <- meanf(italianUnemploymentRate, h = 12)  # h = forecast horizon (e.g., 12 periods ahead)

# View the forecast

MA Model

ma_model <- ma(italianUnemploymentRate, order=3)  # 3-period MA with 12 forecast periods

# View the forecast
ma_forecast <- forecast(ma_model, h = 12)  # 12 periods ahead
## Warning in ets(object, lambda = lambda, biasadj = biasadj,
## allow.multiplicative.trend = allow.multiplicative.trend, : Missing values
## encountered. Using longest contiguous portion of time series
# Plot the forecast
plot(ma_forecast)

Exponential Smoothing

HW_model <- HoltWinters(italianUnemploymentRate)
HW_forecast <- forecast(HW_model, h=8)
plot(HW_forecast)
